<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Throughout the framework, the standard parameter order seems to be "name, object", which is sort of like "key =&gt; value".  For instance, see Zend::register(), Zend_Controller_RewriteRouter::addRoute(), and even PHP internals like __set().  Zend_Cache::save(), however, is "object, name", which seems backwards.</p>

